<p style="text-align:justify;">a private <span class="DelHand-author">&amp; public</span> nature and <span class="AddHand-author">of a public </span>Trust, that I had their confidence when in their employ, &amp; I have retained their Friendship and Patronage when they had no further Occasion for my Services.  These I apprehend will be deemed a good recommendation, and the sure Signs of a fair character.  This Character you have wantonly sported with &amp; wounded; a day of Retribution will come, I live in hopes to see that Day when <span class="AddHand-author">a competent Court will be constituted in which </span>I shall bring you forth to be tried by that Country &amp; by those Laws which <span class="AddHand-author">in traducing me </span>you have scandalised and abused.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Since you have forced me to appear in Public for my own vindication, you must pardon me if I take the liberty to make a few Strictures in return, and by a fair quotation of your own Words <span class="AddHand-author">still to</span> <span class="AddHand-author">strengthen my testimony &amp; to </span>exhibit proof that you had determined to prejudge the motion of M<sup>r</sup> Williams; if words have any import, my construction of them is right.  You declare that the Court on 7th June ordered the motion of M<sup>r</sup> Williams <span class="AddHand-author">(made on that day the 7</span><span class="AddHand-author"><sup>th</sup></span><span class="AddHand-author"> June) </span>to be communicated to M<sup>r</sup> Panet (the Attorney for M<sup>r</sup> Cochrane) <span style="text-decoration:underline;">And that the same should be considered of by the Court</span>.  What! Will the Judge of any Court declare that while the Plaintiff is communicating a Copy of his motion to the Defendant, the Court will be employed in considering that motion, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">alone</span>, in <span style="text-decoration:underline;">secret</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">out of Court</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">before <span class="DelHand-author">hearing</span> </span><span class="AddHand-author"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">knowing</span></span><span style="text-decoration:underline;"> that the Communication</span> is <span style="text-decoration:underline;">given</span>, <span class="AddHand-author">and</span> <span class="AddHand-author">before a </span><span style="text-decoration:underline;">defence </span><span class="AddHand-author"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">was </span></span><span style="text-decoration:underline;">made</span>; Is not this prejudging; is not this</p>

